    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-07-31T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-07-31T22:00:00-05:00" n="767"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d767">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890D.01/621: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Beirut</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gwynn</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-07-31T23:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 31, 1942—11 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>121. Your 264, July 26, 3 p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Your courtesy visit to Damascus prior to delivery of <hi rend="italic"
                            >aide-mémoire</hi> is approved. However, the Department desires to
                        obtain as early as possible the necessary assurances from the Syrian and
                        Lebanese Governments regarding treatment of American individuals and
                        institutions in Syria and Lebanon, in order that decision may be taken on
                        question of recognition. Note has been taken of your comment in this regard,
                        but consideration of a broad nature connected with our general relations
                        with peoples of the Near East render prompt decision desirable if
                        satisfactory assurances of respect for our treaty rights are
                        received.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Change of wording you suggest in paragraph 2 of <hi rend="italic"
                            >aide-mémoire</hi> is approved.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>With reference to your paragraph 7, the Department is not aware of any
                        objection to your continuing to carry on your relations with the Free French
                        authorities in a manner similar to that followed in the past.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
